{"title":"Something about Tensorflow","date":"2020-07-31T15:29:48.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Jul 31, 2020","L":"07/31/2020","MM-DD":"07-31"},"link":"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow","tags":["Tensorflow"],"updated":"2020-07-31T15:37:57.510Z","content":"<p>Some solutions to some common errors about tensorflow.</p>\n\n\n<h2 id=\"1-AttributeError-module-‘tensorflow’-has-no-attribute-‘truncated-normal’\">1 AttributeError: module ‘tensorflow’ has no attribute ‘truncated_normal’<a href=\"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow#1-AttributeError-module-‘tensorflow’-has-no-attribute-‘truncated-normal’\"></a></h2><p>solution: Just replace tf with tf.compat.v1.</p>\n<h2 id=\"2-Error-“Keras-requires-TensorFlow-2-2-or-higher”\">2 Error: “Keras requires TensorFlow 2.2 or higher”<a href=\"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow#2-Error-“Keras-requires-TensorFlow-2-2-or-higher”\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># upgrade tensorflow</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">pip install --user --upgrade tensorflow-gpu</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># upgrade tensorboard</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">pip install --user --upgrade tensorboard</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># Downgrade Keras</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">pip install keras==2.3.1</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># Downgrade tensorflow-gpu</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">pip install --user --upgrade tensorflow-gpu==1.14.0</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"3-LOCAL-DEVICES-tf-config-experimental-list-devices\">3 _LOCAL_DEVICES = tf.config.experimental_list_devices()<a href=\"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow#3-LOCAL-DEVICES-tf-config-experimental-list-devices\"></a></h2><p>AttributeError: ‘module’ object has no attribute ‘experimental_list_devices’</p>\n<p><em>Solution</em>: by modify line 506</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">_LOCAL_DEVICES = tf.config.experimental_list_devices()</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<p>to</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">devices = tf.config.list_logical_devices()</span><br><span class=\"line\">_LOCAL_DEVICES = [x.name <span class=\"keyword\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\">in</span> devices]</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"4-To-see-the-version-of-Tensorflow\">4 To see the version of Tensorflow<a href=\"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow#4-To-see-the-version-of-Tensorflow\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">pip list | grep tensorflow</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"5-ImportError-libcublas-so-10-0-cannot-open-shared-object-file-No-such-file-or-directory\">5 ImportError: libcublas.so.10.0: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory<a href=\"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow#5-ImportError-libcublas-so-10-0-cannot-open-shared-object-file-No-such-file-or-directory\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">conda install cudatoolkit=<span class=\"number\">10.0</span><span class=\"number\">.130</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"6-CMake-Error-Could-not-find-CMAKE-ROOT\">6 CMake Error: Could not find CMAKE_ROOT !!!<a href=\"2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow#6-CMake-Error-Could-not-find-CMAKE-ROOT\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"built_in\">hash</span> -r</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n","prev":{"title":"Data Processing","link":"2020/07/31/Data-Processing"},"next":{"title":"MultiProcessing in Python","link":"2020/07/31/MultiProcessing-in-Python"},"plink":"https://thswind.github.io/2020/07/31/Something-about-Tensorflow/","toc":[{"title":"1 AttributeError: module ‘tensorflow’ has no attribute ‘truncated_normal’","id":"1-AttributeError-module-‘tensorflow’-has-no-attribute-‘truncated-normal’","index":"1"},{"title":"2 Error: “Keras requires TensorFlow 2.2 or higher”","id":"2-Error-“Keras-requires-TensorFlow-2-2-or-higher”","index":"2"},{"title":"3 _LOCAL_DEVICES = tf.config.experimental_list_devices()","id":"3-LOCAL-DEVICES-tf-config-experimental-list-devices","index":"3"},{"title":"4 To see the version of Tensorflow","id":"4-To-see-the-version-of-Tensorflow","index":"4"},{"title":"5 ImportError: libcublas.so.10.0: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory","id":"5-ImportError-libcublas-so-10-0-cannot-open-shared-object-file-No-such-file-or-directory","index":"5"},{"title":"6 CMake Error: Could not find CMAKE_ROOT !!!","id":"6-CMake-Error-Could-not-find-CMAKE-ROOT","index":"6"}],"reward":true,"copyright":{"custom":"禁止转载-非商用-THSWind"}}